            • com.nativelibs4java:opencl4java:jar:1.0.0-RC2 (compile)
              OpenCL4Java / BridJ

              Description: OpenCL4Java is a thin Java wrapper around OpenCL's C API. It uses JNA as its interop layer library, which means it works on all of the (many) JNA-supported platforms (see http://jna.dev.java.net/). It is autogenerated by JNAerator (http://jnaerator.googlecode.com/), so updates to newer OpenCL specs are a matter of seconds. Note that OpenCL4Java is used by JavaCL, an Object-Oriented API that presents OpenCL in a much more practical, powerful and idiomatic way to Java. For more info, please visit http://code.google.com/p/nativelibs4java/wiki/OpenCL.

              URL: http://code.google.com/p/nativelibs4java/wiki/OpenCL
